datasets.name: 53355b19
datasets.query:
WITH 
profile_metrics AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
)
SELECT
  window.start AS Window,
  granularity AS Granularity,
  COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
  COALESCE(slice_value, "No slice") AS `Slice value`,
    `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
  * EXCEPT(window, granularity, slice_key, slice_value)
FROM profile_metrics_inspected
WHERE
  log_type = "INPUT"
  AND quantiles IS NOT NULL
  AND column_name != ":table"
  AND Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
ORDER BY window.start DESC

  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
  AND column_name NOT IN (":table", "prediction", "churn") -- filter out non feature column
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
drift_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_drift_metrics`
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
  AND window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
)
SELECT 
  concat(window.start," - ", window.end) AS Window, 
  granularity AS Granularity,
  COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
  COALESCE(slice_value, "No slice") AS `Slice value`,
    `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,

  AND drift_type = "CONSECUTIVE" -- only consider consecutive drift
  AND window.start = (SELECT Window FROM last_window_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last window

datasets.name: 35225e1e
datasets.query:
WITH 
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
  AND column_name NOT IN (":table", "prediction", "churn") -- filter out non feature column
),
drift_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_drift_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics_inspected) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
exploded_frequent_items AS (
	SELECT
		EXPLODE(frequent_items) AS frequent_item,
		* EXCEPT (frequent_items)
	FROM profile_metrics_inspected
),
frequency_over_time AS (
SELECT
	column_name,
	COALESCE(CAST(frequent_item.item AS STRING), "null")  AS value,
	frequent_item.count AS count,
	count AS total_count,
	window.start AS Window,
  granularity AS Granularity,
  COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
  COALESCE(slice_value, "No slice") AS `Slice value`,
    `model_version`   AS `Model Id`
FROM exploded_frequent_items
WHERE log_type = "INPUT"),
categorical_cols_high_drift AS (
	SELECT column_name 
	FROM drift_metrics_inspected
	WHERE chi_squared_test.pvalue < 0.05
  	AND drift_type = "CONSECUTIVE" -- only consider consecutive drift
  	AND window.start = (SELECT Window FROM last_window_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last window
  	AND column_name != ":table"
),
frequency_rank_last_window AS (
	SELECT 
	-- identifiers
	column_name, Granularity, `Slice key`, `Slice value`, `Model Id`,
	value, count, 
	dense_rank() over (
	partition by (column_name, Granularity, `Slice key`, `Slice value`, `Model Id`) 
	ORDER BY count DESC, value asc
	) AS frequency_rank
	FROM frequency_over_time
	WHERE Window = (SELECT Window FROM last_window_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last window
	AND column_name IN (SELECT * FROM categorical_cols_high_drift)
)

SELECT 
	df1.*, df1.count / df1.total_count AS percent
FROM frequency_over_time df1 JOIN 
(SELECT * FROM frequency_rank_last_window WHERE frequency_rank <= :top_k) df2
ON df1.column_name = df2.column_name 
AND df1.Granularity = df2.Granularity
AND df1.`Slice key` = df2.`Slice key`
AND df1.`Slice value` = df2.`Slice value`
AND df1.`Model Id` = df2.`Model Id`
AND df1.value = df2.value

datasets.name: 1b92b2e7
datasets.query:
WITH 
profile_metrics AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
),
table_profile_over_time AS (
SELECT
  window.start AS Window,
  granularity AS Granularity,
  COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
  COALESCE(slice_value, "No slice") AS `Slice value`,
    `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
  * EXCEPT(window, granularity, slice_key, slice_value,   `model_version`  )
FROM profile_metrics_inspected
WHERE
  log_type = "INPUT"
  AND column_name = ":table"),
threshold AS (
  SELECT 
  Granularity, 
  `Slice key`, 
  `Slice value`, 
  `Model Id`,
  median(count) AS threshold 
  FROM table_profile_over_time 
  GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
  )
SELECT df2.threshold, df1.*
FROM table_profile_over_time df1 
LEFT JOIN threshold df2 
ON df1.Granularity = df2.Granularity
AND df1.`Slice key`=df2.`Slice key`
AND df1.`Slice value`=df2.`Slice value`
AND df1.`Model Id`=df2.`Model Id`

datasets.name: 1cb948fe
datasets.query:
WITH profile_metrics AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
),
flattened_metrics AS (
  SELECT
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    window.start as Window,
    'accuracy_score' AS metric_type,
    accuracy_score AS metric_value,
    granularity,
    COALESCE(slice_key, 'No slice') AS `Slice key`,
    COALESCE(slice_value, 'No slice') AS `Slice value`
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE accuracy_score IS NOT NULL AND Window IS NOT NULL

  UNION ALL

  SELECT
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    window.start as Window,
    'precision_weighted' AS metric_type,
    precision.weighted AS metric_value,
    granularity,
    COALESCE(slice_key, 'No slice'),
    COALESCE(slice_value, 'No slice')
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE precision.macro IS NOT NULL AND Window IS NOT NULL

  UNION ALL

  SELECT
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    window.start as Window,
    'recall_weighted' AS metric_type,
    recall.weighted AS metric_value,
    granularity,
    COALESCE(slice_key, 'No slice'),
    COALESCE(slice_value, 'No slice')
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE recall.macro IS NOT NULL AND Window IS NOT NULL

  UNION ALL

  SELECT
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    window.start as Window,
    'f1_score_weighted' AS metric_type,
    f1_score.weighted AS metric_value,
    granularity,
    COALESCE(slice_key, 'No slice'),
    COALESCE(slice_value, 'No slice')
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE f1_score.macro IS NOT NULL AND Window IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT *
FROM flattened_metrics
ORDER BY 'Model Id', Window, metric_type

  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
),
drift_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_drift_metrics`
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
  AND window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
exploded_cm AS (
  SELECT
    EXPLODE(confusion_matrix) AS pred_label_count,
    window.start AS Window,
    granularity AS Granularity,
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
    COALESCE(slice_value, "No slice") AS `Slice value`
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT Window FROM last_window_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last window
    AND log_type = "INPUT"
    AND column_name = ":table"
)
SELECT
  pred_label_count.*,
  * EXCEPT(pred_label_count)
FROM exploded_cm

datasets.name: da2a46c5
datasets.query:
WITH 
profile_metrics AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
  AND column_name NOT IN (":table", "prediction", "churn") -- filter out non feature column
),
latest_two_windows_in_inspection_range AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT window.start AS Window
    FROM profile_metrics
    ORDER BY Window DESC LIMIT 2
),
granularity_selected AS (
  SELECT granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
drift_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_drift_metrics`
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM granularity_selected)
  AND window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
numerical_cols_high_drift AS (
  SELECT column_name
  FROM drift_metrics_inspected
  WHERE ks_test is NOT NULL -- limit to numerical columns
    
    -- CHANGE METRIC AND THRESHOLDs BELOW TO TUNE DRIFT DETECTION
    
    AND ks_test.pvalue < 0.05
    AND drift_type = "CONSECUTIVE" -- only consider consecutive drift
    AND window.start = (SELECT max(Window) FROM latest_two_windows_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last window
    AND column_name != ":table"
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM granularity_selected)
  AND window.start IN (SELECT Window FROM latest_two_windows_in_inspection_range) -- limit to last two windows
  AND column_name in (SELECT column_name FROM numerical_cols_high_drift) -- limit to columns with high drift
),
latest_two_window_quantiles AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, 
  column_name, quantiles
  FROM profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE isnotnull(quantiles)
),
baseline_profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE log_type = "BASELINE"
  AND isnull(slice_key) AND isnull(slice_value) -- default to "No Slice"
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
  AND column_name in (SELECT column_name FROM numerical_cols_high_drift) -- limit to columns with high drift
),
baseline_quantiles AS (
  SELECT column_name, quantiles
  FROM baseline_profile_metrics_inspected
  WHERE isnotnull(quantiles)
),
latest_two_window_quantiles_exploded AS (
    SELECT Window,
    column_name,
    explode_outer(transform(quantiles, ((value, index) -> (index / 1000 AS quantile,value)))) AS temp
    FROM latest_two_window_quantiles
),
baseline_quantiles_exploded as (
    select "Baseline" As Window,
    column_name,
    explode_outer(transform(quantiles, ((value, index) -> (index / 1000 as quantile,value)))) as temp
    from baseline_quantiles
)
SELECT * EXCEPT(temp), temp.* FROM latest_two_window_quantiles_exploded
UNION ALL
SELECT * EXCEPT(temp), temp.* FROM baseline_quantiles_exploded;

datasets.name: f7ccd7b8
datasets.query:
WITH profile_metrics AS (
  SELECT * FROM `amine_elhelou`.`dbdemos_mlops`.`advanced_churn_inference_table_profile_metrics`
  WHERE window.start >= :`Time Window Start` AND window.end <= :`Time Window End` -- limit to the inspection time window range
  AND   `model_version`   = "*" -- default to all model ids
),
last_window_in_inspection_range AS (
  SELECT window.start AS Window, granularity AS Granularity FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE window.start = (SELECT MAX(window.start) FROM profile_metrics) 
  ORDER BY Granularity LIMIT 1 -- order to ensure the `granularity` selected is stable
),
profile_metrics_inspected AS (
  SELECT * FROM profile_metrics
  WHERE Granularity = (SELECT Granularity FROM last_window_in_inspection_range)
),
fairness_metrics AS ( 
SELECT
    `window`.start AS Window,
    COALESCE(slice_key, "No slice") AS `Slice key`,
    slice_value AS `Slice value`,
    monitor_version,
    granularity AS `Granularity`,
      `model_version`   AS `Model Id`,
    statistical_parity, equal_opportunity, predictive_equality, predictive_parity
FROM profile_metrics_inspected
WHERE slice_value in ("true", "false")
AND column_name = ":table"
AND log_type="INPUT"
),
fairness_metrics_unpivot AS (
SELECT 
  * EXCEPT(metric_values),
  explode(metric_values.difference) AS (grp, difference) 
FROM fairness_metrics unpivot (
  metric_values FOR Metric IN (statistical_parity, equal_opportunity, predictive_equality, predictive_parity)
  )
)
SELECT
  Metric,
  grp AS `Positive Class`,
  difference,
  `Model Id`,
  Window,
  `Granularity`,
  `Slice key`
FROM
  fairness_metrics_unpivot
ORDER BY Window DESC

widget.name: d3928946
widget.textbox_spec:
## Profiling
Explore the numerical and categorical profile to understand the shape of the features.

invisibleColumns.name: PSI
invisibleColumns.title: PSI
invisibleColumns.description: Quantifies how much a variable's distribution has shifted between two samples, helpful for monitoring changes in variables or model features over time.

invisibleColumns.name: WD
invisibleColumns.title: WD
invisibleColumns.description: Measures the amount of "work" to transform one distribution into another, effective for evaluating the cost to move a distribution.

frame.title: Features with Numerical Drift in the Last Time Window
frame.description: We use the KS test p-value to determine statistically significant drift. You can configure the test used with the underlying query. If "No Data" is shown, then no features have high drift.

invisibleColumns.name: TVD
invisibleColumns.title: TVD
invisibleColumns.description: Measures the difference between two probability distributions by calculating the absolute difference of their CDFs, useful for anomaly detection in continuous data.

invisibleColumns.name: LID
invisibleColumns.title: LID
invisibleColumns.description: Measures the independence of items in a dataset, detecting drift in categorical profiles by identifying changes in item dependencies.

invisibleColumns.name: JSD
invisibleColumns.title: JSD
invisibleColumns.description: Measures the similarity between two probability distributions, useful for detecting drift in categorical profiles by identifying changes in distribution similarity.

frame.title: Features with Categorical Drift in the Last Time Window
frame.description: We use the Chi-square p-value to determine statistically significant drift between categorical variables. You can configure the test used with the underlying query. If "No Data" is shown, then no features have high drift.

widget.name: abeb12c9
widget.textbox_spec:
#### We compute 4 Fairness Metrics:

1. predictive_parity:
Measures whether the two groups have equal precision across all predicted classes.
model_id_col required
predictive_equality

2. predictive_equality:
Measures whether the two groups have equal false positive rate across all predicted classes.
model_id_col required
equal_opportunity

3. equal_opportunity: 
Measures whether the two groups have equal recall across all predicted classes.
model_id_col required
statistical_parity

4. statistical_parity: 
Measures whether the two groups have equal acceptance rate. Acceptance rate here is defined as the empirical probability to be predicted as a certain class, across all predicted classes.
